outputs.output_descr:
•Reduce acute food insecurity and save lives of vulnerable households;
•Protect, restore and improve household food and livelihoods security of vulnerable populations for self reliance;
•Restore and promote sustainable Natural Resource Management (NRM) by vulnerable communities;
•Strengthen coordination of interventions, capacity of partners, emergency preparedness and effective response to Food Security and Livelihoods hazards.

•Contribute to improved access to acceptable quality of prevention, care, and treatment of acute malnutrition for populations with critical nutrition situations or conflict affected areas
•Contribute to the strengthening of MoH and partners capacity to identify, prepare for and respond to and mitigate nutrition problems  in emergencies;
•Expansion of women's and children's access to evidence based high impact and feasible nutrition related services for populations in crisis by empowering communities and finding durable solutions

